  "India": {
    "title": "Diss Track on Indian Restaurants",
    "body": "Dear College,\n\nI’m sorry this place is your depiction, let me be honest\nIt takes spice to call it spice6, that place is not responsive\nI look at it and wish that a chipotle had been promised\nSorry to everyone at the counter, front and behind it\n\nAnd you’re a good city that needs good leadership\nLet me educate you since Spice6 didn’t teach you this\nNever let a shop serve you roti that’s just bread, son\nEither you make it right or call it how it’s said, son\n\nNever try and cater to too many people, that’s bad business\nPlease remember, food is only rich if it is made with penance\nNever lose your identity, whether right or wrong you are indian\nEven if it doesn’t benefit your goal, be strong, find your discipline\n\nDon’t cut corners like what spice6 did, too many things in it\nThere’s no calling it a naan pizza, And then hiding the indian \nWhat even is a naan pizza, cheese, tomatoes and bread again\nMight as well call it naan and paneer, that’s what it is in sheepskin\n\nDon’t be ashamed of your heritage, it’s demeaning if I may\nWhat you should be ashamed of is charging 18 for lamb filet\nMediocre food tastes like ass, I can hear the donkey’s bray\nNot ethnic enough to deserve a Mahabarat, this diss is your play\n"
  },
